From 99d545bb5c8e6ef6d7161682678dc96fd12a26dc Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Enrique Parodi Spalazzi <enrique.parodi@airbus.com>
Date: Fri, 24 Apr 2026 00:19:19 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 07/10] fix[term]: SQL error UX and duplicate query-name
 rejection

Two polish items on top of the Stage 3 integration:

- Underline the invalid span: query_highlight::buildRuns takes a list
  of error spans; tokens that overlap one get the error style (red
  underline) even if their kind is otherwise unstyled.
- Errors are surfaced only on a submit attempt, not while typing.
  Showing them live reads as the parser complaining about a
  half-typed query. The prompt symbol still flips red live as a
  subtle binary cue, but the underline and inline message wait for
  ESC-free Enter. Revealing clears automatically the next time the
  buffer changes.
- Inline error message: after a blocked submit, the first error
  diagnostic's message is rendered on a dedicated row under the
  input (not inline, so long messages do not get clipped on narrow
  terminals). The grammar hint is suppressed while the error row is
  visible. Moving the caret into a specific span swaps the message
  to that span's diagnostic.
- Reject duplicate query names across all sources: createQuery now
  walks every open source instead of just the target session.bus,
  since 'query rm <name>' and the subscription map both key on the
  short name.
